We apply this transformation methodology to the kinetic simulation of hybrid magnetic reconnection, and transform the results of the RMHD simulation at t = 0.8 ns to the PIC simulation, see Supplementary Fig. 2 and Supplementary Fig. 4. Balance the computing power and the universality, we choose the mass of Cu ions in the PIC simulation to be mCu = 1000me, and the mass of CH ions mCH and He ions mHe are calculated proportionally, which gives fm ~ 0.0085. The parameters of number density fn = 10 and temperature fT = 5. These parameters lead to t1/t0 ~ 0.0012, i.e., 1.2 ps in PIC simulations represents 1.0 ns in RMHD simulations and experiments. In the PIC simulations, the ion charge state Z¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
